remarks: A native field corn was found to have some typical sweet corn characteristics. It was backcrossed, selfed and resel- lected for productivity, tender kernels, and other desire- able characteristics. Vigorous, tall gorwing 8-9 ft., highly resistant to Yellow Stripe mosaic disease, Helminthosporium leaf spot, & Stewart's disease.  Agri. in th Americas, Vol.6 No.4, April 1946. Resrch. Achievement sheet. 114(0) Nov.1948

remarks: A native field corn was found to have some typical sweet corn characteristics. It was backcrossed, selfed and resel- lected for productivity, tender kernels, and other desire- able characteristics. Vigorous, tall gorwing 8-9 ft., highly resistant to Yellow Stripe mosaic disease, Helminthosporium leaf spot, & Stewart's disease.  Agri. in th Americas, Vol.6 No.4, April 1946. Resrch. Achievement sheet. 114(0) Nov.1948
